 Consuelo wishes she could share her First Communion this year with Abuelita.
 She misses her grandmother very much.
 Consuelo and Abuelita aren't actual people, but their story nevertheless is played over and over again among the more than 3 million Latinos in the Los Angeles metropolitan area, health officials say.
 Nationwide, it is estimated that there are more than 2 million Latinos who already have diabetes, many of them undiagnosed.
 Like heart disease, the adult-onset diabetes most common among Latinos is a condition that can be largely prevented with proper diet and exercise, doctors say.
